title: 820-00165 Magsafe not turning on
message:
[B]Board: [/B]820-00165

[B]Issue: [/B]Magsafe not turning on. No light on magsafe, putting out about 2v. 

[B]Background: [/B]
Initially came in for no power, liquid damaged around ISL area, as well as PPDCIN_G3H_ISOL area. 

Replaced ISL, cleaned up PPDCIN_G3H_ISOL area. Unit worked fine. Came back a week later, no signs of life. When plugging in an Original magsafe 2, It puts out the 2v. When I plug in my Magsafe from the DCPS, the unit boots up with no issue.

[B]What I've checked/Done:[/B]
R7012 has the correct measurement of 68k
Trace from R7012 to DCIN connector is okay
Measurement between pin 1 and 6 at the connector are 68k

Replaced DCIN connector, as it had corrosion on the pins.

Not exactly sure where to go next

title: 820-00165 Magsafe not turning on
message:
If machine boots with lab PSU, or fake charger, then you have leakage issue.
Usually Q7180, or D7012.

title: 820-00165 Magsafe not turning on
message: Thank you guys, it was Q7180
